| API               | Payload       | Speed           | Notes          |
| ----------------- | ------------- | --------------- | -------------- |
| REST              | JSON + Base64 | Slowest         | Human readable |
| tRPC              | JSON          | Faster          | Type safe      |
| gRPC              | Protobuf      | Fastest         | Binary         |
| gRPC Microservice | Binary        | Slight overhead | Scalable       |

Performance Analysis

1️⃣ Simulated Measurements
| Method                | Response Time (ms) | Payload Size               | Network Calls / Batching            | Type Safety / Integration Ease              |
| --------------------- | ------------------ | -------------------------- | ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| **REST**              | 3–5                | JSON (larger)              | Single/batch supported              | Easy to implement, no type safety           |
| **tRPC (conceptual)** | 2–4                | JSON (slightly smaller)    | Single/batch supported              | Type-safe with TypeScript, easy integration |
| **gRPC unary (mock)** | 1–3                | Protobuf (binary, smaller) | Single request                      | Requires setup, high efficiency             |
| **gRPC microservice** | 2–4                | Protobuf (binary)          | Internal calls (service-to-service) | Decoupled, scalable, requires setup         |

Notes:

Numbers are simulated from our mock API Service using endToEndMs.

Payload size: JSON is text-based (larger), Protobuf is binary (smaller).

Network calls: REST/tRPC can handle batches; gRPC unary is usually one request per call.

Type safety: tRPC > gRPC > REST (for TypeScript projects).

2️⃣ Conceptual Comparison
| Feature                  | REST       | tRPC          | gRPC unary      | gRPC microservice |
| ------------------------ | ---------- | ------------- | --------------- | ----------------- |
| Serialization efficiency | Low (JSON) | Medium (JSON) | High (Protobuf) | High (Protobuf)   |
| Ease of implementation   | Easy       | Medium        | Medium          | Medium/Hard       |
| Scalability              | Medium     | Medium        | High            | Very High         |
| Decoupling               | Low        | Medium        | High            | Very High         |
| Type safety              | None       | Strong        | Medium          | Medium            |

